# =============================================================================
# NodeShare — production / “live purchase” configuration
# =============================================================================
# 1) Copy this file:  cp .env.example .env.local   (Windows: copy .env.example .env.local)
# 2) Replace every placeholder with real values (never commit .env.local).
# 3) Run:  npm run verify-env
# 4) Run:  npm run build && npm run start
#
# On Netlify: Site → Environment variables → add the same keys (all deploy contexts).
# Do NOT set STATIC_IPFS_EXPORT on Netlify — export:ipfs sets it only on your PC.
#
# --- Production checks ---
# Netlify: Deploys → latest succeeded. Visit
# https://YOUR-SITE.netlify.app/api/build-info — ethRpcProbe should be ok: true.
# IPFS / *.eth.limo: re-run npm run export:ipfs + new CID + ENS contenthash when UI changes.
#
# --- IPFS static export (optional) ---
# When you run `npm run export:ipfs`, set this to your Netlify origin (serves /api/*):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE=https://nodesharev1.netlify.app
# =============================================================================

# --- Public site URL (canonical links, future emails) ---
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://your-domain.com

# --- Ethereum JSON-RPC (required for live balances) ---
# Create: https://dashboard.alchemy.com/ or https://infura.io/ → Ethereum Mainnet endpoint
# Server-only; never expose admin keys in NEXT_PUBLIC_* except the browser RPC below.
ETH_RPC_URL=https://eth-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR_ALCHEMY_KEY

# Browser must be able to call this RPC for “Send USDC/USDT” (same URL is fine).
# In Alchemy/Infura: restrict key to your site origin + Ethereum Mainnet only.
NEXT_PUBLIC_ETH_RPC_URL=https://eth-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR_ALCHEMY_KEY

# --- Etherscan (required for live USDC/USDT transaction list) ---
# Use unified API V2 only (legacy V1 is deprecated). Create at etherscan.io/myapikey
# — paste with NO quotes/spaces in Netlify. If you see Invalid API Key (#err2), create a fresh key.
ETHERSCAN_API_KEY=YOUR_ETHERSCAN_KEY

# Chain (default 1 = Ethereum mainnet). Must match RPC + contracts.
CHAIN_ID=1
NEXT_PUBLIC_CHAIN_ID=1

# Optional — defaults are canonical mainnet USDC / USDT (6 decimals)
# USDC_CONTRACT_ADDRESS=0xA0b86991c6218b36c1d19D4a2e9Eb0cE3606eB48
# USDT_CONTRACT_ADDRESS=0xdAC17F958D2ee523a2206206994597C13D831ec7

# --- Render (OPTIONAL — many accounts cannot get API access) ---
# If unset, the dashboard “Render (live)” card explains that Render isn’t wired.
# If you later get access: Render → Account → API Keys → key starting with rnd_
# RENDER_API_KEY=rnd_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# --- Akash LCD (optional — app rotates several public REST nodes if unset) ---
# Override if your region blocks defaults or you want one trusted REST origin only:
# AKASH_LCD_URL=https://api.akashnet.net
